The paper discusses the construction of efficient radial basis functions (RBFs) using problem features, which is a topic related to numerical analysis (cs.NA) and machine learning (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of operator-dependent RBFs, which falls under the category of supervised learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses problem-dependent and time-space distance functions, which are relevant to scientific computing (cs.SI) and data structures (cs.DS).
